An immersive experience for Advisory professionals entering the Senior level. The design of the program focuses on advanced consulting skills that are applicable across our Advisory business to help build skills, build leadership skills and make them more productive on engagements. It consists of a 5-day, instructor-led learning event composed of integrated and complex case study exercises, multiple team activities, technology-enabled micro-simulations, group discussions supported by lecture, as well as self-directed learning and activities to be completed in advance of the classroom session. Based on a simulated Advisory client engagement, this highly interactive learning is designed to give staff practical experience addressing real-world challenges and situations supported by coaching, feedback and frequent opportunities to strengthen their advanced consulting skills.

results.Short_x0020_description: Lack of effective change management is a key factor in most program failures. results.Title: Introduction to Business Process Improvement
results.Short_x0020_description:
Process improvement is about understanding the key drivers within any given business and developing a clearer understanding of the end-to-end business process in order to fully understand that business.
All businesses are built on a set of processes to manage the time, cost and quality of the delivery of any goods or services. Business processes often evolve and change as customer demands change, as businesses grow and systems and technologies become outdated, but they are rarely examined end-to-end.

results.Title: Enterprise Architecture and TOGAF 9

results.Title: Internal Audit Transformation
results.Short_x0020_description:
The purpose of this learning is to provide participants with the knowledge, tools and enablers to identify opportunities for IAT services and to deliver these services. The course is designed as a three day course:

1. Day 1 of the learning, through a combination of lecture/presentations and facilitated group discussions and activities, will provide participants with an overview of the Internal Audit (IA) market, IAT service offering and IA framework. It will provide an opportunity to explore IA leading practices, demonstrating the linkage between IAT to IA leading practices and the RISK agenda. IA leading practices will be discussed for each element of the IA framework (IA strategy, core delivery methodology, people model, support processes, measurable impact and leverage enterprise intelligence). Working in mixed-level teams, participants will complete two activities designed to identify leading practices in the context of a realistic IA function, and apply these leading practices to build and prioritize a high level IAT work plan on case study based on a real client.

2. Days 2 and 3 will allow participants to work through a case study that is threaded throughout the two days. Days 2 and 3 will be linked to Day 1. Anchored by brief lecture presentations, the focus of the activities on Days 2 and 3 will be on applying the process and change management principles/ theory underlying the IAT methodology. The case study will include supporting materials such as wall charts, handouts and videos, and it will encompass activities related to identifying IAT opportunities, validating the current state, co-developing future state and project level roadmap with the client and developing a program level roadmap.

results.Title: Sales and Operations Planning
results.Short_x0020_description: Sales and Operations planning (SandOP) is an integrated business management process developed in the 1980s through which the executive/leadership team continually achieves focus, alignment and synchronization among all functions of the organization. SandOP includes an updated forecast that leads to a sales plan, production plan, inventory plan, customer lead time (backlog) plan, new product development plan, strategic initiative plan and resulting financial plan. Done well, the SandOP process also enables effective supply chain management. The EY SandOP class is designed to provide participants an understanding of the fundamentals of the process, the EY point of view and how to position SandOP with client. This course is not designed to redesign the methodology, teach project management fundamentals, provide detailed tools instruction, coach sales fundamentals, or provide technical application controls training.

results.Short_x0020_description: The Advisory Introduction to Project Management ILT course is a three-day, interactive instructor-led training (ILT) course intended for global deployment to Advisory professionals. It is recommended for seniors, managers or any experienced person who desires or needs an introduction to Advisory’s approach to project management — in particular, those who are about to lead projects. The objective is to establish a standardized approach to project management across EY and to improve project management knowledge and skills, both for individuals and across Advisory.

results.Title: Advisory Foundations Onboarding
results.Short_x0020_description: The Americas Advisory Foundations course is intended for new hires — senior through manager. This course will provide you an overview of Advisory, reaffirm your decision to join the firm and provide you with the information you will need to do your job correctly. You will be introduced to Ernst and Young’s (EY) culture and processes using experiential learning. This allows you to “learn by doing” through networking with your peers, utilizing the tools, methods and resources you use on the job so you will know how to operate in the firm and the Advisory practice and what is required of you as an EY Advisory professional. This includes how EY documentation works within the context of the Advisory tools and enablers and the Qualify, Plan, Deliver, and Close (QPDC) phases of the engagement lifecycle.

results.Title: Advisory Immersion
results.Short_x0020_description: Advisory Immersion is a three-day rapid assessment experience for experienced new hires. In Advisory Immersion participants, as members of developing high performing teams, are immersed in the Current state – Future state assessment service method (CFAM) to explore current state issues and recommend improvement opportunities to achieve the case client’s desired future state. This course applies the SOLVE approach to problem solving and incorporates the CTQR approach to structured communication to define the client’s problems and provide a structured response. Through immersion, participants also gain practical experience in key consulting activities such as interviewing clients and presenting the proposal to senior executive level clients.

results.Title: Advisory Immersion Global Version
results.Short_x0020_description: Advisory Immersion is a three-day rapid assessment experience for experienced new hires. In Advisory Immersion participants, as members of developing high performing teams, are immersed in the Current state – Future state assessment service method (CFAM) to explore current state issues and recommend improvement opportunities to achieve the case client’s desired future state. This course applies the SOLVE approach to problem solving and incorporates the CTQR approach to structured communication to define the client’s problems and provide a structured response. Through immersion, participants also gain practical experience in key consulting activities such as interviewing clients and presenting the proposal to senior executive level clients.

results.Title: Advisory Revenue Recognition - Process and Systems Assessment
results.Short_x0020_description: Two day instructor led course to train PI professionals on the diagnostic phase of revenue recognition projects. The course introduces the new revenue recognition standard, outlines its implications to companies, and explains how the accounting diagnostic factors into the greater operating model assessment. Participants will learn the process and system assessment methodology, how to properly scope client needs, and will be introduced to the design and implementation phases.

results.Title: Business Processes in SAP ERP and S/4HANA
results.Short_x0020_description: This course explores the foundational concepts of the main business processes we come across at our clients. While the course is focused on business processes for SAP applications; the concepts taught as part of this training are applicable to other ERP systems (e.g., Oracle, PeopleSoft, BAAN, Lawson, etc.).

results.Title: COBIT 5 for Information Security
results.Short_x0020_description: This is a one day course that will provide an overview of COBIT®5, ISACA’s new governance framework and how it can be adapted to enable management of Information Security. The course provides an overview of how the generic COBIT® 5 framework is adapted for Information Security, the twelve principles recommended for good Information Security Practices, seven enablers to support Information Security, and how to apply COBIT 5 principles. After successful completion of this course you will be able to apply the COBIT principles and enablers to assess and make recommendations for improvement, design and implement governance and management of information security.

results.Title: Creating Winning Proposals
results.Short_x0020_description: Creating Winning Proposals explores a sales-focused approach to writing within the context of EY. It looks at how to construct proposals that address the readers' needs and reflect the value that EY delivers. It explores how to create attractive, convincing documents that engage the reader and win business.

results.Title: CRS Contract Risk Services
results.Short_x0020_description: This course provides staff and seniors a grounding in Contract Risk Services. This course features the following topics: a) CRS Overview b) Q&RM Considerations c) CRS methodology and planning d) GTH overview and capabilities e) Engagement execution f) Engagement reporting

results.Title: Data Protection Training
results.Short_x0020_description: Data Protection refers to the full suite of processes and controls to protect an organization’s data, both from internal and external threats. This course will cover the components of a data protection program and the capabilities and applications of data loss prevention technologies.

results.Title: EY Advanced Consulting (Canada)
results.Short_x0020_description: EY Advanced Consulting is a training event for the new senior inside the EY Advisory practice. Its aim is to teach new seniors the critical tasks inherent to their position as well as best practices for optimizing performance improvement as it relates to EY clients. Participants will be engaged in a five-day, instructor-led learning event composed of classroom sessions, complex case study exercises and group discussions.

results.Title: EY Core Consulting
results.Short_x0020_description: To prepare learners to effectively demonstrate core consulting skills, the program is designed to immerse learners in an environment closely representing situations that they will encounter while working on Advisory engagements. Throughout the program learners will be instructed on subject matter via lectures, eLearning formats (video, traditional web-based learning, etc.), and facilitated discussions. However, the primary source of learning for the participants will come from applying knowledge of the subject matter during frequent and intensive activities. Real-time feedback, debrief discussions, and coaching delivered by facilitators will reinforce learning.

results.Title: EY Core Consulting
results.Short_x0020_description: To prepare learners to effectively demonstrate core consulting skills, the program is designed to immerse learners in an environment closely representing situations that they will encounter while working on Advisory engagements. Throughout the program learners will be instructed on subject matter via lectures, eLearning formats (video, traditional web-based learning, etc.), and facilitated discussions. However, the primary source of learning for the participants will come from applying knowledge of the subject matter during frequent and intensive activities. Real-time feedback, debrief discussions, and coaching delivered by facilitators will reinforce learning.

results.Title: FAIT Immersion
results.Short_x0020_description: FAIT Immersion is a 2½-day basic training that prepares participants to support our Assurance (Channel 1) clients on financial audit engagements. The course covers key technical concepts, including risks and controls, IT environment elements, IT general controls walkthroughs, testing, and evaluation, application controls strategy and testing, IT audit strategy, and current topics affecting the audit climate, such as inspection themes. The course also provides an introduction to our Topic Global Audit Methodology (GAM), our audit tool (Canvas) and explores the resources and enablers that will help participants perform the day-to-day activities that will be expected on a client engagement.

results.Title: Foundations privacy and data protection training
results.Short_x0020_description: A course for Advisory professionals to become familiar with EY privacy related services and laws and resources for privacy related engagements

results.Title: Introduction to COBIT 5
results.Short_x0020_description: This is ISACA's one-day, ""Introduction to COBIT5"" course that will provide an overview of COBIT5, ISACA's new governance framework. The course provides existing practioners and potentioal new COBIT5 users insight into the new framework and explains the differences between COBIT4.1 and COBIT5. You will understand the principles of enterprise IT and explain the differences between governance and management. The course will also describe the basics of how to implement COBIT5 and what your clients should consider in the transition from COBIT4 to COBIT5. The course is recommended for those preparing for additonal COBIT5 training, including the COBIT5 Foundation Course, COBIT5 Implementation COURSE Assessor Program Training - all of which include the ability to earn COBIT5 certificates. Additionally, this will prepare you for providing the ""Introduction to COBIT5"" course at your clients and is a prerequisite to “COBIT 5 for Information Security”.

results.Title: Introduction to Data Analytics using ACL
results.Short_x0020_description: Introduction to Data Analytics using ACL is targeted for Staff and Senior Advisory professionals. This course will provide foundational training needed for professionals involved with the planning, execution, and delivery of data analytics projects. The course will cover the Data Analytics methodology and will teach basics of ACL.

results.Title: Introduction to Supply Chain Planning
results.Short_x0020_description: This course will help build a robust foundation of knowledge for EY’s client serving professionals to identify and support the improvement of their client’s supply chain planning organizations. EY resources should be able to understand the key concepts of demand and supply planning, recognize the sales & operations planning framework. They should also be able to identify KPI’s, gaps in planning processes and how each domain affects the other. Finally, they should understand the role technology plays in etching out a high performing planning organization.

results.Title: Oracle GRC Controls Fundamentals
results.Short_x0020_description: This three-day course will introduce participants to the four governors that comprise the Oracle GRC Controls suite. Participants will gain an understanding of the firm's methodology and leading practice techniques for the implementation and functionality of the entire suite.

results.Title: RA400: FAIT Intermediate Skills
results.Short_x0020_description: The RA400: Financial Audit IT (FAIT) Intermediate Skills consists of 2 components. The first component is the ONLINE PREREQUISITE (click the hyperlink to access a PDF with instructions on how to complete this component), which MUST be completed before you can register for the second component, the in-class Instructor Led Training (ILT) RA400: Financial Audit IT (FAIT) Intermediate Skills training.

results.Title: Seniors Advancing in Leadership (SAIL)
results.Short_x0020_description: This course is a 1.5 day interactive, instructor-led training (ILT) course intended for senior 2/3s. This is an intensive, experiential leadership development course for this audience. This course utilizes a case study-based design focusing on defining moments in the development of an Advisory leader, and includes instruction on important inputs to leadership development such as communication styles/personality instruments and reinforcement of the firm’s values and culture initiatives

results.Title: SAP Processes
results.Short_x0020_description: The SAP Processes course enables Advisory Risk professionals to improve the quality of our audits by examining end-to-end processes of Order to Cash (OTC), Purchase to Pay (PTP) and Financial Statement Close Process (FSCP) and identifying risks and controls in relation to SAP processes. Participants also test the design and operating effectiveness of the SAP controls.

results.Title: ThinkTank Designer
results.Short_x0020_description: This ThinkTank Designer Course is divided into two parts. The first is the online portion that is a required prerequisite to attend the second part, the Instructor Led Training (ILT). The online exercises take place within the ThinkTank platform and feature a combination of short tutorial videos and interactive activities followed by a brief WBL assessment. Once you have completed the assessment, you can register for the second part, which is the one-day classroom session follow-up.

results.Title: ThinkTank Designer
results.Short_x0020_description: El presente curso presenta una serie de temas de gran relevancia para los colaboradores de EY de manera que puedan desarrollar a lo máximo su potencial brindando los mejores servicios a los clientes de la firma.

results.Title: KFT: Building Client Relationships (External sources)
results.Short_x0020_description: The session is intended to be hands-on with participants following along on their own laptops, using their clients or pursuits as backdrop. During the session, participants will learn how to quickly locate Account Management Framework materials, thought leadership resources and industry insights. The class experience is expected to be conversational and fast-paced with overviews of several useful tools. Topics in this session include: Keep up with your account, Keep up with sector thought leadership and knowledge, Winning in the Market CHS, Resources and tips for mobile users.

results.Title: KFT: Connect, Team and Share (External sources)
results.Short_x0020_description: The course provides an overview of the new collaboration tools and demonstrates how to connect with colleagues, find information and collaborate with others. Covering where we are and where we are going, it is designed to increase understanding of our new environment and solutions. Tools used: Collaboration tools, SharePoint collaboration solutions, team site, community, project site, People Profile, My Site.

results.Title: KFT: Finding Company Information (External sources)
results.Short_x0020_description: ​You will learn how to proceed with company research based on your task and entity's status, and which resource to select: corporate websites, SPARK-Interfax, OneSource, Factiva, ThomsonOne.com

results.Title: KFT: Finding Industry Information (External sources)
results.Short_x0020_description: The session helps to understand EY industry sectors, and provides an overview of internal and external resources available for your own industry research. Discover tips on use of Factiva, ThomsonONE.com, Business Monitor and others.

results.Title: KFT: Using Knowledge Sources to Build Proposals and Win Work (External sources)
results.Short_x0020_description: The course provides an overview of the resources available to support practitioners when they are building proposals to help EY win work: Discover,Yammer, Sector sites, EY Home Page - About EY and ey.com, DCRO, SPARK-Interfax and others.

results.Title: Macroeconomic data: effective locating and retrieving (virtual session)
results.Short_x0020_description: The course is designed to help EY practitioners locate sources of macroeconomic information and provide tips on how to retrieve and process that information.

results.Title: CRM Training
results.Short_x0020_description: A 2 hours session covers key CRM protocols and the end-to-end opportunity management processes – from initial point of contact with the client, through the funnel stages, to GTAC assessment and Engagement setup

results.Title: Archiving in Advisory
results.Short_x0020_description: During this course participant will learn how to use databases, search for client’s cases and  all requirements for archiving  at Advisory department

results.Title: CIS Advisory Onboarding for New Hires
results.Short_x0020_description: The Advisory Onboarding course is intended for new hires — Intern through Senior. This course will provide an overview of Advisory, reaffirm your decision to join EY and provide the information you will need to do your job correctly. You will be introduced to EY’s culture and processes using experiential learning.

results.Title: MS Excel Advanced Level
results.Short_x0020_description: The training is designed to sharpen and deepen your knowledge of MS Excel. The training based only on practical exercises.

results.Title: Planning and Time Management
results.Short_x0020_description: This practice-based training provides applicable  instruments that help participants become more effective with their day-to-day tasks. The training covers a number of skills including: setting clear goals, defining priorities and daily planning.

results.Title: QRM for Advisory
results.Short_x0020_description: During the course following topics will be covered: Quality and Risk Management framework, Service Quality program, client/engagement acceptance, engagement agreement supervision & review, engagement documentation and archiving.

results.Title: Storyboarding & Slide Design
results.Short_x0020_description: The training is designed to introduce the way we structure our deliverables. It is aimed at explaining the form that our deliverable takes, and some of the processes that we use to produce it. Training is focused on both: content and visualization.

results.Title: Management 101
results.Short_x0020_description: The objective of the course is to provide participants with a high level understanding of their duties, responsibilities and expected skill set as managers not only through theoretical materials, but mostly through practical exercises

results.Title: Proposal 101
results.Short_x0020_description: The course teaches the basics of how to put together a winning proposal and includes a review of mandatory proposal contents, common practices as well as mistakes to avoid.

results.Title: Supply Chain Fundamentals
results.Short_x0020_description: This course helps new practitioners and experienced practitioners understand how to conduct Supply Chain and Operations (SC&O) transformation projects. The course provides an overview of the global trends affecting our clients’ SC&O agenda and looks at EY’s positioning in the advisory market and at our approach to transformation projects. Finally, we use the tools and capabilities that are available across the global EY network to transform a sample client’s SC&O approach and positively impact its financial and overall performance.

results.Title: Advanced Client Interaction
results.Short_x0020_description:
This workshop addresses the preparation, execution and
follow-up aspects of client communications. It emphasizes
preparing for and conducting client meetings and stresses
participation during role-play and case study activities.

results.Title: Business Writing at EY: Structure
results.Short_x0020_description:
A workshop designed to develop a strategic approach to
writing. It explains an effective technique for structuring
thinking and writing, giving opportunities to apply. During
the course, participants explore ways of using language
clearly and concisely and practice techniques for writing
summaries and headings.

results.Title: Business Writing at EY: Style
results.Short_x0020_description:
This course introduces the principles and techniques
needed to write effectively at EY. It explores ways
of using structure and language to meet the needs
of readers of EY documents — whether strategists,
managers or “doers".

results.Title: Coaching for Enhanced Performance
results.Short_x0020_description: This is a one day practical workshop introducing you to the fundamental concepts and skills of coaching. The workshop has been designed to be highly interactive and in each lesson, you will have an opportunity to discover how to apply the learning to your role at EY

results.Title: Counselor Workshop
results.Short_x0020_description:
The workshop provides knowledge and practice for
new counselors. It focuses on the role of the counselor, both in terms of participating in the formal PMDP process as well as in the day-to-day counselor role. The workshop covers a number of skills including: giving effective feedback, delivering difficult messages, setting SMART goals, developing questioning, listening and coaching skills

results.Title: Creating Client Connections
results.Short_x0020_description:
Research has shown that our clients have different styles
— meaning they employ varying approaches to problems
and challenges, relationship building and event managing
their time. This means we have to adjust our style in
order to succeed.

results.Title: Effective Client Encounters
results.Short_x0020_description:
It is important in every client encounter that our
professionals demonstrate an account-centric,
issue-based focus and approach. This will result in better
understanding of the client’s issues and priorities and
allow us to more effectively align our resources and
services. This course provides a reliable methodology
to more effectively prepare, conduct and debrief client
meetings and encounters.

results.Title: Effective Presentations
results.Short_x0020_description:
Effective Presentations is a two-day, interactive in classroom workshop designed to increase the confidence,
know-how and skills of EY’s professionals to develop and
deliver presentations for maximum audience impact.
This workshop is constructed to enable presenters
to determine exactly what they want their audience
members to know, feel and do as a result and to achieve
just that, whether the audience is internal or external.

results.Title: Managing High Performing Teams
results.Short_x0020_description: This course is aimed at managers who have some experience working in and leading teams. In a highly interactive way, it practices key skills which managers need to set up their teams for success and to develop them to high performance.

results.Title: Interviewing Skills
results.Short_x0020_description: This course helps participants determine how to use interviewing techniques (e.g. STAR).

results.Title: Strategic Opportunity Management
results.Short_x0020_description:
Strategic opportunity management offers a proven
methodology and approach for gathering essential
information and developing winning strategies for
high-value opportunities.

results.Title: Delegation & feedback
results.Short_x0020_description: Delegation and Feedback are important skills for good leadership. Delegation provides more focus for your job and offers challenges for the jobs of more junior co-workers. Feedback is an important tool in discussing development and improvement with people. Both leadership skills contribute tremendously to the ability of the organisation to change, to develop new professionals and to deliver Quality in everything.

results.Title: Effective Negotiations
results.Short_x0020_description: The course is about negotiations beyond agreeing on the price. It deals with co-developing service quality expectations while establishing the best economic outcome for the client and the firm. The training covers concepts of BATNA and Multiple Options and their usage in pursuits and in negotiations

results.Title: Engagement Economic Decisions and their Impact
results.Short_x0020_description:
The aim of this course is to provide an environment where
participants can learn and practice all that goes into
managing engagement economics successfully.

results.Title: Engagement Economics and GFIS
results.Short_x0020_description: GFIS is a set of web-based financial applications used for creating and maintaining engagements, reporting on time charged, amounts billed and fees collected from our clients. We can also use GFIS to measure the financial performance of work done for our clients

results.Title: Facilitator Development Workshop
results.Short_x0020_description: This course prepares participants for their responsibilities as EY instructors. The content focuses primarily on presentation and facilitation techniques but also includes information about critical success factors for learning.

results.Title: Versatility in Depth
results.Short_x0020_description:
Versatility in Depth is a “deeper-dive” look at versatility
for participants who already have been introduced to the
TRACOM SOCIAL STYLESSM model in the Creating Client
Connections course.

results.Title: Virtual Facilitation
results.Short_x0020_description:
For learning in the virtual setting to be effective, your role as a facilitato of virtual classrooms is of great importance. Whether you’re an experienced face-to-face classroom facilitator or new to the facilitation world, there are new skills that you can learn to make your virtual classrooms interactive, engaging, effective and great learning places to be.
This course will introduce you to those skills and give you lots of
opportunities to practice them. At the end of this course, you will be much more confident and able to run effective learning sessions in the virtual-classroom environment. This course is specifically targeted at people who have already been nominated to facilitate a virtual classroom-based course using the WTC platform.

results.Title: Successful Virtual teams
results.Short_x0020_description: This course helps participants determine how to build Successful Virtual teams.

results.Title: CIS New Senior Program
results.Short_x0020_description:
The New Senior Program is designed to help participants
understand the requirements and expectations of their
new role. It focuses on some of the key skills they will
need to develop, and enhance, to be effective senior

results.Title: Introduction to Highest Perfoming Teams
results.Short_x0020_description:
High Performing Teams helps participants develop their
leadership and team management skills from the initial
stages of building a team through to high performance.

results.Title: CIS New Manager Program
results.Short_x0020_description: New Manager Program is designed to help participants understand the requirements of their new role and build a strategy for success. It focuses on skills immediately needed in their new role.

results.Title: Fundamentals of Internal Audit (IA)
results.Short_x0020_description: The purpose of this course is to enable all seniors and first-year managers to perform an Internal Audit project within a co-source/outsource engagement. Emphasis is on developing work products and deliverables (service delivery).

results.Title: Global Procurement Intermediate
results.Short_x0020_description: Participants will learn about key and consistent Supply Chain analytics needed to perform end-to-end analysis, including data manipulation, presentation of graphs and charts, interpretation of trends, provision of narrative and “so-whats," and to recognize common analysis pitfalls so they can be avoided.

results.Title: RA100: FAIT Foundations
results.Short_x0020_description: This 3.5-day training prepares participants to support our Assurance (Channel1) clients on financial audit engagements. The course covers key technical concepts, including risks and controls, IT environment elements, ITgeneral controls, and how IT supports a financial audit. The course also provides an introduction to our Global Audit Methodology (GAM), our audittool (EY Canvas) and explores the resources and enablers that will help participants perform the day-to-day activities that will be expected on a clientengagement.

results.Short_x0020_description: This course provides practical information about the security administration, program change, and IT operations as they relate to SAP ECC 6.0.

results.Short_x0020_description: Handle Data Efficiently; Reduce occurrence of errors; Produce reliable conclusions; Convey your conclusions in an appropriate way

results.Title: EY Core Consulting - SA Region
results.Short_x0020_description:
The EY Core Consulting program for Staff provides an immersive
onboarding experience for our new Advisory hires at the staff level. This
program helps them to quickly gain an understanding of our approach to
delivering exceptional client service and working in high performing
teams, while demonstrating EY values. The design of the program
focuses on core consulting skills that are applicable across our Advisory
business to help accelerate our staff resources' integration into the firm
and make them productive on engagements. It consists of a 9-day,
instructor-led learning event composed of integrated and complex case
study exercises, group discussions supported by lecture, as well as selfdirected
learning and activities to be completed in advance of the
classroom session. Based on a simulated Advisory client engagement,
this highly interactive learning is designed to give staff practical
experience addressing real-world challenges and situations supported by
coaching and frequent opportunities to strengthen their core consulting
skills.

results.Title: EY Advanced Consulting - SA Region
results.Short_x0020_description:
The EY Advanced Consulting program provides an immersive learning
experience for new Senior consultants. The program’s goal is to teach
Seniors critical team leadership skills of effective delegation, coaching
and feedback, as well as to enhance their development across the
Advisory-wide competencies. Throughout the course, participants are
challenged to act in the role of an Advisory Senior by thinking critically,
communicating effectively and understanding how the Advisory practice
provides value to our clients. The course consists of a 5-day, instructorled
learning event that includes multiple team activities and technologyenabled
micro-simulations, in addition to lecture and group discussions.
